{
  "texts": [
    "Each droplet is carefully separated by either an antisolvent or an inert gas, thus providing every droplet with the functionality of an individual reactor.",
    "This segmentation ensures precise control over reactions and prevents interference between different reaction environments.",
    "Moreover, the ratio of reagents within these droplets is easily modulated using syringe pumps, providing users with a convenient means to collect data efficiently and coherently.",
    "This approach streamlines experimentation processes, enhances reproducibility, and facilitates the exploration of complex reaction spaces with unprecedented accuracy.Droplet microfluidics has emerged as a powerful tool across diverse scientific disciplines, with dedicated literature offering concepts behind droplet formation [41,42].",
    "An example of a segmented flow droplet system was employed to screen a range of organic solvents to obtain optimal conditions for the monoalkylation of trans-1,2-diaminocyclohexane [43]."
  ]
}